August	15,	2022	
AFTER	ACTIVITY	REPORT	
I.	BACKGROUND:	
TESDA	Guimaras	has	set	its	targets	and	plans	for	CY	2022	based	on	the	National	Technical	
Education	and	Skills	Development	Plan	(NTESDP),	Presidential	and	Secretary	’sDirectives,	
region-specific	programs,	new	legislation	for	implementation,	relevant	researches	and	inputs	
from	stakeholders	among	others.	The	TESDA	Corporate	Plan	2019-2022	served	as	the	
guide	to	all	operating	units	in	program	implementation	for	FY	2022	to	ensure	attainment	of	
the	goals	and	objectives	of	the	TESD	Plan.	
TESDA	Circular	Number	28	series	of	2015	states	that	TESDA	Strategic	Performance	
Management	System	operates	on	shared	commitments	and	objectives	measures	of	
performance	results.	Thorough	the	OPCR	and	IPR	performance	contracting	documents,	
performance	targets	and	standard	of	measures	of	results	-outputs/outcomes	-are	planned	
and	agreed	upon	by	management,	supervisors	and	employees.	Performance	evaluation	are	
conducted	semi-annually	covering	the	rating	periods	January	to	June	and	July	-December	
2022.	The	TESDA	SPMS	recognizes	that	shared	values	and	individual	competencies	are	
needed	to	attain	the	authority	’svision,	mission	and	goals.	
The	TESDA	SPMS	operates	on	a	team	approach	to	performance	management.	
Accountabilities	and	individual	roles	in	the	achievement	of	organizational	goals	are	clearly	
defined	to	give	way	to	collective	goal	setting	and	performance	rating.	Individual	Performance	
Commitment	and	Review	form	is	linked	to	the	Office	Performance	Commitment	and	Review	
(OPCR)	form	which	in	linked	to	the	TESDA	corporate	OPCR	to	establish	clear	linkage	
between	organizational	performance	and	employee	performance.

Republic	of	the	Philippines	
TECHNICAL	EDUCATION	AND	SKILLS	DEVELOPMENT	AUTHORITY	
ISO	9001:2015	Certified	
Region	VI–Guimaras	Provincial	Office	San	Miguel,	Jordan,	Guimaras.	Zip	Code	5045	Cell	No.	09175090676/09985737353	Telephone	No.	(033)-5812194	E-mailaddress:	region6.guimaras@tesda.gov.ph	
II.	OBJECTIVES:	
1.	To	orient	each	personnel	of	the	set	indicators	and	targets	for	each	Programs,	Projects	and	
Activities.
2.	Review	of	the	programs,	projects	and	activities	together	with	the	evidences	required	for	
each	accomplishments	
III.	HIGHLIGHTS:	
A	calibration	of	the	Individual/Office	Performance	Commitment	and	Review	was	
implemented	on	August	15,	2022	at	TESDA	Guimaras	Provincial	Office	Conference	Room.	
The	activity	was	attended	by	the	personnel	of	the	Provincial	Office	and	training	center.	Ms.	
Laarni	D.	Pavillon,	Supervising	TESD	Specialist	presented	the	2022	planning	guidelines	of	
TESDA.	The	Strategic	Performance	Management	System	Guidelines	was	discussed	
emphasizing	on	the	success	indicators	for	each	output.	Success	indicators	are	performance	
level	yardstick	consisting	of	performance	measures	and	performance	targets.	This	shall	
serve	as	the	basis	in	the	office	and	individual	employee	’spreparation	of	their	performance	
contract	and	rating	form.	
The	category	on	how	performance	are	measured	are	through,	effectiveness/quality,	
efficiency	and	timeliness.	Ms.	Pavillon	explained	that	effectiveness	or	quality	is	defined	to	
the	extent	to	which	actual	performance	compares	with	targeted	performance.it	is	also	the	
degree	to	which	objectives	are	achieved	and	the	extent	to	whjicg	targeted	problems	are	
solved.	Efficiency	is	the	extent	to	which	time	or	resources	are	used	for	the	intended	task	or	
purpose.	Timeliness	measures	whether	the	deliverables	was	done	on	time	based	on	the	
requirements	of	the	law/or	clients/stakeholders.	
Evidences	required	for	each	indicators	were	presented	to	the	attendees	to	determine	how	
accomplishments	must	be	measured

