In-Country Program on "Research Methodology for TVET 

Leaders and Teachers" 	

The Colombo Plan Staff College (CPSC) is inviting Technical Education and Skills 	

Development Authority (TESDA) to the virtual In-Country Program on 	
"Research 	

Methodology for TVET Leaders and Teachers" 	
on March 13 to 17, 2023. 	

This program aims to teach the participants the fundamental concepts and methods 	

of research methodology and its scientific process. 	

The CPSC is inviting TESDA to nominate thirty (30) qualified applicants based on 	

the following criteria: 	

a. 	
High-level government officials such as Directors, Administrators, Chief TESD 

Specialist, Supervising TESD Specialist, and trainers; 	

b. 	
Holds a bachelor\'s degree; 	

c. 	
With at least one (1) year of continuous service as a permanent employee of 

TESDA; 	

d. 	
With no administrative pending case; 	

e. 	
Has at least Very Satisfactory performance for the last two rating periods; and 	

f. 	
Must be proficient in English both written and spoken. 	

Please submit the names of your recommendee/s to the TESDA Development 	

Institute (TDI) email address: tdi@tesda.gov.ph 	
not later than 	
January 23, 2023. 	
